==English==
===Etymology===
from French [[quatre]] 'four' + [[corner]]
===Pronunciation===
IPA (''US''): /ˈkɪtiˌkɔrnər/
===Adverb===
'''kitty-corner'''
# (with ''to'':) located [[diagonal]]ly across from something, especially across an [[intersection]]
#* The library is '''kitty-corner''' to the supermarket.